title: For Sale:  Custom Smith & Wesson M&P9 Range Kit
postcontent:
The M&P Range Kit is a popular and hard to find in 9mm.  This one is in perfect condition (I’ve owned it less than 2 months) and has an upgraded trigger by Apex Tactical.

If you read any reviews about the M&P everyone is quick to point out how gritty the stock trigger is.  In addition, people complain that there’s too much take up and no positive reset upon release of the trigger.  The upgraded trigger kit by Apex Tactical fixes all of this and includes a Glock-style trigger and safety, Forward Sear Set, and Reset Assist Mechanism (RAM).  The parts alone for this trigger job cost over $160 (I can show you the receipt if you’d like).

From Apex’s website, the trigger kit yields:
•	“Reduced trigger pre-travel and over travel to produce a feel similar to a single action fire control system.”
•	“A smooth trigger pull all the way through to the break.”
•	“Improved safety values through the use of a center mounted pivoting safety.”
•	”4lbs or 5.5lbs depending on which trigger return spring is installed with the kit.”

They have this to say about the RAM upgrade:
“The Apex Reset Assist Mechanism (Patent Pending) is a drop in part engineered to improve tactile trigger reset of your M&P pistol.  Along with improving the felt reset, the Apex RAM also serves as a failsafe in the unlikely event of a Trigger Return Spring breakage; keeping the trigger bar properly positioned under the sear and allowing the user to manually manipulate the trigger forward between shots.”

The trigger is amazing on this firearm now.  The only reason why I’m selling it is that despite acclaims of how great the grip feels I finally accepted that it just isn’t for me (I have long, slender fingers and a childhood finger injury that makes me pickier than most).

I currently have the 5.5lb trigger spring installed, but you could swap it for the 4lb one if you’d like.  I also have all of the original factory trigger parts if you ever want to re-install them.

In addition to the superb trigger job, this includes everything in the standard kit:
•	Blade-Tech® Kydex® Holster
•	Blade-Tech® Double Magazine Pouch
•	Maglula Uplula™ Speed Loader
•	3 Magazines (MA-Compliant 10-RND)
•	Cable Lock
•	Carry Case
•	Manual
•	3 different back straps to customize pistol grip

Why buy new when you can buy used and already have the trigger that you’re going to want anyway?  I’ll knock $25 off of the price if you don’t want/need the Uplula speed loader since I wouldn’t mind keeping that.  Otherwise, price for everything is $635 cash (no trades).  You must have a LTC-A to purchase (or even look at) this firearm.  We can do the transfer privately, or at a FFL at your expense.

DISCLAIMER:  By responding to this ad you agree that the Seller is not a lawyer and does not claim to offer legal advice on what is legal in Buyer’s jurisdiction.  Nor does Seller claim to offer advice on what modifications may or may not be appropriate for self-defense or any other purpose.  Buyer assumes all legality, liability and responsibility for the condition, use & security/storage of the firearm purchased.

postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=50

Item 4B (300gr. JFN) is designed for super deep penetration at revolver speeds, but will mushroom and penetrate less deeply at rifle speeds. At handgun speeds you can expect a solid 3 feet of penetration in muscle and bone and at rifle speeds expect roughly 2 feet of penetration in muscle and bone. At handgun velocities, this bullet will act just like item 4A in living tissue. The greater velocities generated by the longer barrel of the rifle will cause the bullet to mushroom and that large mushroom will make a much bigger diameter hole in tissue, but that frontal area on the mushroomed bullet will cut down the depth of penetration.
You’ll note my below velocities form over-the-counter revolvers and rifles.
1.       Ruger Super Blackhawk with 6 inch barrel--------1330 fps
2.       Ruger Redhawk 5.5 inch barrel-----------------------1334 fps
3.       1894 Marlin with 18.5 inch barrel---------------------1770 fps
Item 4B is recommended for all STEEL revolvers and rifles on today’s market. It is NOT suitable for scandium or aluminum alloy revolvers.
